  <br>
&quot;Knowledge!..  Ha!..&quot;  For a thousand thousand years he had seen the process of life, and the follies of those who'd not survived as he.  &quot;What I can share is tales, but the knowledge must be gleamed from them yourselves.&quot; <br>
  <br>
&quot;Then share you tales and I shall listen with a keen ear.&quot; proclaimed the sand giant.  &quot;If there is Knowledge there, I shall not miss it, of that I am certain.&quot;  The boldness in the young giant's statements irked the ancient cyclops.  What story to tell he wondered...  Then this one came to him.... <br>
  <br>
In the mountains of Rathe there was a pair.   One a Hill giant of great power and the other a cyclops of growing age and wisdom.  They often conversed and found game together, but this day was not to be their own. <br>
  <br>
&quot;There are intruders in our domain&quot; the hill giant shared with the cyclops eagerly.  He enjoy crushing the little people and watching them squirm as most giants do. <br>
&quot;Where, good friend?&quot;  as a cyclops the passing of intruders is seldom missed, but these he had not seen. <br>
  <br>
<br>
&quot;Follow and I shall show you.&quot;  The hill giant lead his partner around their favored hunting grounds to the outer side of the valley where the four little ones sat unaware of the eyes upon them...  &quot;See there, a wee barbarian, two tiny elves and a stinking human.&quot; <br>
  <br>
<br>
A smile drew across the cyclop's face, &quot;Let's smoosh them.&quot; and with a smirk and a touch of laughter they charged in on the wee ones. <br>
  <br>
&quot;Little Man, Little man, Filled with red!...  I will crush your bones when you are dead!&quot; laughed the cyclops as his hand swatted at the wee ones. <br>
  <br>
<br>
&quot;Shit!...  This is going to hurt.&quot;  the human warrior of his 29th season cried to his 3 friends. <br>
  <br>
<br>
&quot;Everyone on the hill giant!&quot;  Cried the desperate elven bard as her eye drifted to her dear friends.  She would not fail them this day she vowed as she worried over her newest 31st song. <br>
  <br>
<br>
&quot;Your foul deeds have not gone unnoticed Silverron!&quot; growled the hill giant and he felt a slight poke of the fool hearty elf's halberd. <br>
  <br>
<br>
A song rose to the cyclop's ears.  It beckoned him, &quot;Love me as I love you....  My love is yours and you love is mine....  Protect me my love...  Love me...  Save me.&quot;  and the cyclops felt it in his heart.  The elf woman, so small and so lovely.  He did love her, he knew he did.  &quot;My pet attack him&quot; a blue hand gestured to the hill giant brutalizing the wee ones.  <br>
  <br>
<br>
&quot;Don't taunt!&quot; cried the bard to her fellows. <br>
  <br>
<br>
The hill giant turned at his fellow, &quot;What are you doing?&quot; He asked as he returned blows to the crazed cyclops.  And the cyclops found his wits, turning on the wee elf who's music had dimmed his wits. <br>
  <br>
<br>
